Class PropertyMapperList

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.Scrollable
public class PropertyMapperList
extends javax.swing.JList

This class is a customization of JList that is intended to contain only property mapper list items and render them appropriately. This is intended to be used on a property mapper panel.

Author:
Eric Marinier

getListConsistency

public boolean getListConsistency(java.lang.Class<?> listClassType)
Determines whether or not this list is consistent. More specifically, that every item in this list are of the same class type. If the list has no elements, it will return true. If the list contains only elements that are all the same as the passed listClassType, it will return true. If the list contains any elements that have a different class type, it will return false.

Parameters:
listClassType - The class type to check consistency for.
Returns:
Whether or not the list is consistent.
